<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Location </div></div>
The '''Ferronix Silicate''' is commonly found in areas with strong electrical activity, vibration, or large amounts of metal infrastructure. Small shards are seldom discovered near nonfunctioning generators, broken illumination devices, elevator shafts, ventilation tunnels, server rooms, and abandoned industrial machinery. The crystals typically grow upon conductive materials such as copper wiring, steel supports, and metallic walls. In darker environments, '''Ferronix''' can be identified by their subtle greenish yellow glow and its low humming sound.

Large formations are drastically rarer, and are typically located deep inside unstable industrial areas, or, heavily damaged mechanical sectors. These clusters usually grow in symmetrical forms and may cause nearby electronics to flicker or malfunction.

'''Ferronix Silicate''' has been recorded to be found in:
* [[Level 1]]
* [[Level 2]]
* [[Level 3]]
* [[Level 5]]
* [[Level 8.1]]
* [[Level 14]]
* [[Level 15]]
* [[Level 17]]
* Et cetera

Many groups, mostly such as [[A.D.F.]], and [[Architect Industries]], collect '''Ferronix Silicate''' because of its ability to generate electricity. Stable deposits are deemed valuable resource sites and are usually guarded, mined, or salvaged for crystal fragments.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Discovery </div></div>
'''Ferronix Silicate''' was allegedly first discovered by the [[A.D.F.]] during an infrastructure recheck within a deteriorating area of their facility whose lighting systems had reportedly been lit in spite of the absence of visible power sources. Former reports described electricity fluctuations, subtle humming, and repeated electrical equipment failures occurring throughout the area.

The discovery itself occurred after an [[A.D.F.]] maintenance team dismantled a collapsed wall section near an inactive generator chamber. Behind the structure, they found several dark crystal formations embedded directly into the metal framework of said wall. At first, the formations were dismissed as their abandoned former technology. However, deeper inspectation revealed the crystals generated raw electricity independently, without batteries, fuel, or external power. This unusual behavior led to the material being classified as an unique anomalous compound.

Henceforward, [[A.D.F.]] began extracting '''Ferronix''' samples for research and testing. Thus, they eventually developed the first ever stabilized crystal configuration. As the understanding of the crystal improved overtime, '''Ferronix Silicate''' rapdily became second of their most valuable resources.
</div>

